   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://www.fukt.bth.se/~per/identd/$SOURCE
        WEB_SITE=http://www.fukt.bth.se/~per/identd/
       BUILD_API=2
         ENTERED=20020105
         UPDATED=20020115
     SOURCE_HASH=sha512:3f533933da0d3be42713ee3ab18a31c72c19434363635b3a996ad1a0b7516eb3a2127f181b4c584a19671ae4e270ab6248a2c975b6e8ae26817990bee3c3bab4
        KEYWORDS="net"
           SHORT="linux-identd is a very small user identification daemon."
cat << EOF
linux-identd is a user identification daemon for Linux, which implements
the Identification Protocol (RFC1413). This protocol is used to identify
active TCP connections. The daemon listens to TCP port 113 (auth), and
can be run either as a stand-alone daemon, or through inetd.
EOF
